2 Raw data

2.1 Load the data

Read the sample information

samples <- read.csv("~/Git/UPSCb/projects/facility-immanen-et-al/doc/PRJEB13583-Ctl-bestaligned frc.csv")
samples$othernames <- sprintf("AF%02d",as.integer(sub("AF","",samples$othernames)))
ord <- order(samples$Tree,samples$othernames)
samples <- samples[ord,]

Read the HTSeq results

res <- mclapply(dir("htseq",pattern="*.txt",full.names=TRUE),function(fil){
  read.delim(fil,header=FALSE,stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
},mc.cores=max(mcaffinity()))

Rename them

names(res) <- sub("_sortmerna.*\\.txt","",dir("htseq",pattern="*.txt"))

Select the one we need

res <- res[names(res) %in% samples$SampleID]

Re order the data

res <- res[match(samples$SampleID,names(res))]
#samples <- samples[match(names(res),samples$SampleID),]

Extract the count table

addInfo <- c("__no_feature","__ambiguous","__too_low_aQual","__not_aligned","__alignment_not_unique")
sel <- match(addInfo,res[[1]][,1])
count.table <- do.call(cbind,lapply(res,"[",2))[-sel,]
colnames(count.table) <- names(res)
rownames(count.table) <- res[[1]][,1][-sel]
dir.create(file.path("analysis","HTSeq"),recursive = TRUE, showWarnings = FALSE)
write.csv(count.table,"analysis/HTSeq/raw-unormalised-data_ctrl-selected frc.csv")

2.3.2 Estimate the number of expressed genes

vsd <- varianceStabilizingTransformation(dds, blind=TRUE)
vst <- assay(vsd)
vst <- vst - min(vst)
write.csv(vst,"analysis/HTSeq/library-size-normalized_variance-stabilized_PRJEB13583_ctl-selected_frc-data.csv")

3 Conclusion

The data quality looks better now, however there is an effect of the sequencing depth that becomes shallower as samples got from the phloem to the xylem. This resulted in less genes having their expression recorded as the samples went inwood. This effect was counterbalanced by the library size estimation, resulting in a technical increase of the average gene expression values for many genes as samples were going inwards the wood. This needs to be corrected for, if possible, as it will be confounded with real biological changes.
